# Layout width

Use these terms and classes when building or requesting project page sections:

| Mode | Class | Width | Use for |
|------|-------|-------|---------|
| **full-width** | `layout--full` | 100% viewport | Heroes, backgrounds, banners, edge-to-edge composites |
| **contained** | `layout--contained` | 80% viewport, centered | Media stacks, content blocks with shadow/margins |

CSS tokens: `--layout-full-width`, `--layout-contained-width`.

Apply width classes on **inner wrappers**, not always on `<section>`, so section backgrounds can remain full-width while content is contained.

When the user says "full-width" or "contained", use the matching class without re-negotiating the convention.
